comment: Integration by parts. If ` B ( x ) ` is the derivative of ` A ( x ) ` and ` D ( x ) ` is the derivative of ` C ( x ) ` , and ` E = ( A x. B ) ( X ) ` and ` F = ( A x. B ) ( Y ) ` , then under suitable integrability and differentiability assumptions, the integral of ` A x. D ` from ` X ` to ` Y ` is equal to ` F - E ` minus the integral of ` B x. C ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 3-Sep-2014.)
